title: Biden backs plan to provide F-16 fighter jets to Ukraine
description: During the G7 summit, President Joe Biden and European allies promised new support for Ukraine, agreeing to provide American F-16 fighter jets. NBC News’ Molly Hunter has the story.

title: At least 12 dead in stampede at soccer stadium in El Salvador
description: Officials say at least 12 people are dead and about 100 others injured after a stampede during a soccer match at Cuscatlán Stadium in San Salvador, El Salvador.

title: Greece votes in first election since international bailout spending controls ended
description: Greeks were voting Sunday in the first election since their country’s economy ceased to be subject to strict supervision and control by international lenders who had provided bailout funds during its nearly decade-long financial crisis.

title: Pakistani trans activists to appeal Shariah court ruling against law aimed at protecting them
description: Transgender activists in Pakistan said they plan to appeal to the highest court in the land an Islamic court’s ruling that guts a law aimed at protecting their rights.

title: The G-7 shows China's rise prompting assertive new alliances in its own backyard
description: The United States and its allies hoped to showcase their “commitment to peace” at the Group of Seven summit this weekend in Hiroshima, the Japanese city rebuilt from the irradiated ashes of an American atom bomb.

title: Extremist Israeli Cabinet minister visits sensitive Jerusalem holy site
description: An extremist Israeli Cabinet minister visited a sensitive Jerusalem holy site on Sunday at a time of heightened tensions with the Palestinians.

title: At least 9 dead in crush at soccer stadium in El Salvador
description: At least nine people were killed and dozens more injured when soccer fans pushed through one of the access gates at a quarterfinal match in the Salvadoran league Saturday.

title: Warring factions in Sudan agree to temporary ceasefire, U.S.-Saudi mediators say
description: Sudan’s warring factions have agreed to a new short-term ceasefire, U.S. and Saudi mediators announced on Saturday, after several previous attempts to broker a truce that holds have failed.

title: British novelist Martin Amis dies at 73
description: British novelist Martin Amis, who brought a rock ‘n’ roll sensibility to his stories and lifestyle, has died.
